  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.000" end="00:00:07.280" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, visitors. This is a video to talk
<br />about how to cross your Ts.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:07.280" end="00:00:10.980" tts:direction="ltr">Now that's an important element when it
<br />comes to storytelling,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:10.980" end="00:00:16.680" tts:direction="ltr">and that includes these two concepts of
<br />takeaway titles and tool tips.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:16.680" end="00:00:20.060" tts:direction="ltr">Those are all the Ts and let's dive into
<br />the very first one,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:20.060" end="00:00:21.955" tts:direction="ltr">which is a takeaway title.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:21.955" end="00:00:25.230" tts:direction="ltr">Talked already about how in a design
<br />schema,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:25.230" end="00:00:31.030" tts:direction="ltr">that upper left hand corner is really
<br />important real estate for your chart.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:31.030" end="00:00:33.590" tts:direction="ltr">But now let's talk about a takeaway title.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:33.590" end="00:00:36.370" tts:direction="ltr">A takeaway title is the opportunity for
<br />you to</p>
        <p begin="00:00:36.370" end="00:00:39.730" tts:direction="ltr">really provide an insight into your
<br />visualization.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:39.730" end="00:00:42.410" tts:direction="ltr">Here are four things to consider.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:42.410" end="00:00:46.330" tts:direction="ltr">The first one is whenever possible to use
<br />an action verb.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:46.330" end="00:00:50.830" tts:direction="ltr">An action verb will incite some action.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:50.830" end="00:00:53.950" tts:direction="ltr">We want to use that and harness that
<br />whenever possible.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:53.950" end="00:00:57.030" tts:direction="ltr">We want to show don't tell.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:57.030" end="00:01:00.470" tts:direction="ltr">Often we default to our telling headline</p>
        <p begin="00:01:00.470" end="00:01:04.630" tts:direction="ltr">that here is the information that we're
<br />going to share,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:04.630" end="00:01:06.790" tts:direction="ltr">and it's a very basic headline.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:06.790" end="00:01:08.830" tts:direction="ltr">Instead, focus on that showing,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:08.830" end="00:01:10.270" tts:direction="ltr">use in that action verb.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:10.270" end="00:01:16.510" tts:direction="ltr">89% of users prefer the orange ball cap.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:16.510" end="00:01:20.455" tts:direction="ltr">Then your chart, your data supports that
<br />takeaway title.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:20.455" end="00:01:24.700" tts:direction="ltr">Sometimes you might want to use questions
<br />if you're exploring the data.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:24.700" end="00:01:26.940" tts:direction="ltr">If you're using exploratory dashboard,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:26.940" end="00:01:28.620" tts:direction="ltr">there might be a question to say</p>
        <p begin="00:01:28.620" end="00:01:32.700" tts:direction="ltr">which cap is preferred by our younger
<br />audience.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:32.700" end="00:01:34.920" tts:direction="ltr">That might elicit more questions from</p>
        <p begin="00:01:34.920" end="00:01:38.120" tts:direction="ltr">your audience and that exploratory
<br />modality.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:38.120" end="00:01:40.280" tts:direction="ltr">Then finally, it's important to tell</p>
        <p begin="00:01:40.280" end="00:01:43.320" tts:direction="ltr">the user to use a filter if it's
<br />available.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:43.320" end="00:01:47.160" tts:direction="ltr">Click on the filter to select other
<br />audiences or</p>
        <p begin="00:01:47.160" end="00:01:51.245" tts:direction="ltr">click the drop down so that they know that
<br />there's some interactivity.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:51.245" end="00:01:54.730" tts:direction="ltr">When it comes to crossing your Ts and your
<br />takeaway title,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:54.730" end="00:01:59.270" tts:direction="ltr">here's an example from a product where
<br />they're determining whether or</p>
        <p begin="00:01:59.270" end="00:02:04.010" tts:direction="ltr">not to bring it to market and through some
<br />customer testing,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:04.010" end="00:02:09.410" tts:direction="ltr">they found out that more yogurt and less
<br />fruit was needed in the product.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:09.410" end="00:02:12.590" tts:direction="ltr">The takeaway title is really that action,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:12.590" end="00:02:14.490" tts:direction="ltr">and then it's supported by all this</p>
        <p begin="00:02:14.490" end="00:02:18.545" tts:direction="ltr">additional chart making and some
<br />additional text.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:18.545" end="00:02:22.160" tts:direction="ltr">This is an explanatory story,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:22.160" end="00:02:25.940" tts:direction="ltr">so it has more of that beginning middle
<br />and end feel to it.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:25.940" end="00:02:28.600" tts:direction="ltr">But what if I wanted to do a takeaway
<br />title</p>
        <p begin="00:02:28.600" end="00:02:31.880" tts:direction="ltr">for a dashboard where there's a lot more
<br />exploratory.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:31.880" end="00:02:38.180" tts:direction="ltr">I want to show you this awesome dashboard</p>
        <p begin="00:02:38.180" end="00:02:45.640" tts:direction="ltr">that is showing the beat on recorded music
<br />revenue, and it's 1973-2018.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:45.640" end="00:02:48.320" tts:direction="ltr">You have this title,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:48.320" end="00:02:52.260" tts:direction="ltr">the beat, and then you have this 60
<br />billion USDA.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:52.260" end="00:02:55.140" tts:direction="ltr">That's the total amount spent thus far.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:55.140" end="00:02:57.760" tts:direction="ltr">That is the takeaway that there is a lot
<br />of money</p>
        <p begin="00:02:57.760" end="00:03:02.220" tts:direction="ltr">spent in the music industry or actually
<br />received.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:02.220" end="00:03:05.720" tts:direction="ltr">That's the big takeaway and leading with
<br />that number.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:05.720" end="00:03:07.440" tts:direction="ltr">Now, because it's exploratory,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:07.440" end="00:03:11.840" tts:direction="ltr">I don't want to provide too much
<br />commentary because I want my user to go</p>
        <p begin="00:03:11.840" end="00:03:17.080" tts:direction="ltr">through and to look at where there might
<br />be some peaks and some valleys.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:17.080" end="00:03:20.400" tts:direction="ltr">You'll also notice that there is some
<br />really good tooltips.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:20.400" end="00:03:22.120" tts:direction="ltr">We'll talk about that just a moment.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:22.120" end="00:03:23.940" tts:direction="ltr">For instance, in 1991,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:23.940" end="00:03:27.020" tts:direction="ltr">Cassette had 5.8 billion of revenue,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:27.020" end="00:03:31.870" tts:direction="ltr">41% of that total revenue was in the
<br />singles,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:31.870" end="00:03:33.610" tts:direction="ltr">and the cassettes, and other tapes.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:33.610" end="00:03:36.870" tts:direction="ltr">A really good example also of the tool
<br />tip.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:36.870" end="00:03:41.490" tts:direction="ltr">But there are these micro takeaway titles
<br />here.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:41.490" end="00:03:43.490" tts:direction="ltr">For instance, in the 1980s, it says,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:43.490" end="00:03:46.010" tts:direction="ltr">no more eight track, hello CDs,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:46.010" end="00:03:47.870" tts:direction="ltr">and they've used color there and</p>
        <p begin="00:03:47.870" end="00:03:52.590" tts:direction="ltr">a really good marker of where that resides
<br />within the dashboard.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:52.590" end="00:03:56.050" tts:direction="ltr">A dashboard has a lot more freedom when it
<br />comes to</p>
        <p begin="00:03:56.050" end="00:04:00.170" tts:direction="ltr">those takeaway titles and not so much in
<br />that prescriptive story line.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:00.170" end="00:04:03.290" tts:direction="ltr">Let's jump back into the presentation.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:03.290" end="00:04:07.370" tts:direction="ltr">And look at this particular dashboard.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:07.370" end="00:04:10.090" tts:direction="ltr">This is a personal training program
<br />dashboard,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:10.090" end="00:04:11.790" tts:direction="ltr">where there's a lot of data.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:11.790" end="00:04:13.630" tts:direction="ltr">What I want to do is I want to show you
<br />this</p>
        <p begin="00:04:13.630" end="00:04:16.090" tts:direction="ltr">before so we can look at the after.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:16.090" end="00:04:19.770" tts:direction="ltr">There are some colors, I've got a tal on
<br />one side and blue on another.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:19.770" end="00:04:21.490" tts:direction="ltr">I've got client registrations,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:21.490" end="00:04:23.470" tts:direction="ltr">I've got active clients by week.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:23.470" end="00:04:26.290" tts:direction="ltr">There is a lot going on in this dashboard,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:26.290" end="00:04:28.590" tts:direction="ltr">and honestly, the data is good.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:28.590" end="00:04:31.630" tts:direction="ltr">It's just not as accessible as it could
<br />be.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:31.630" end="00:04:34.070" tts:direction="ltr">If we move to this one where there's been</p>
        <p begin="00:04:34.070" end="00:04:37.890" tts:direction="ltr">some more design intentionality and
<br />they're crossing their ts,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:37.890" end="00:04:42.500" tts:direction="ltr">you can begin to see that you've got your
<br />major metrics up here on top.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:42.500" end="00:04:46.470" tts:direction="ltr">You have your registrations and sessions
<br />by week, which by the way,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:46.470" end="00:04:49.250" tts:direction="ltr">they're using a tal right here in</p>
        <p begin="00:04:49.250" end="00:04:52.250" tts:direction="ltr">registrations and matching that also with
<br />the line.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:52.250" end="00:04:54.930" tts:direction="ltr">That can remove the key or the legend.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:54.930" end="00:04:57.310" tts:direction="ltr">Then you have total registrations by week,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:57.310" end="00:05:00.350" tts:direction="ltr">we're using that active to show where that
<br />lies.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:00.350" end="00:05:04.870" tts:direction="ltr">Then we've grade out the sessions
<br />engagement by location right here,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:04.870" end="00:05:06.870" tts:direction="ltr">and then also by trainer.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:06.870" end="00:05:09.260" tts:direction="ltr">Now, You're probably wondering,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:09.260" end="00:05:14.340" tts:direction="ltr">where are the takeaway titles in this
<br />particular exploratory dashboard.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:14.340" end="00:05:18.400" tts:direction="ltr">That's really in the presentation or
<br />within the tool tips,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:18.400" end="00:05:21.040" tts:direction="ltr">where I can point out that here there are</p>
        <p begin="00:05:21.040" end="00:05:24.860" tts:direction="ltr">fewer weekly registrations and sessions
<br />since launched in May.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:24.860" end="00:05:30.140" tts:direction="ltr">I'm pulling out an actual statistic that
<br />I'm seeing for the drop.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:30.140" end="00:05:32.800" tts:direction="ltr">Right here, I can see that center C has</p>
        <p begin="00:05:32.800" end="00:05:36.200" tts:direction="ltr">the highest number of registrations and
<br />percents of clients.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:36.200" end="00:05:38.240" tts:direction="ltr">Again, I'm lifting some of those out.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:38.240" end="00:05:40.520" tts:direction="ltr">I can pull them here if I need to,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:40.520" end="00:05:42.160" tts:direction="ltr">but because it's exploratory,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:42.160" end="00:05:44.380" tts:direction="ltr">it's really a chance for me to articulate
<br />that in</p>
        <p begin="00:05:44.380" end="00:05:48.435" tts:direction="ltr">my storytelling and then let my user drill
<br />down a bit deeper.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:48.435" end="00:05:51.890" tts:direction="ltr">Now I can take one of those charts and I
<br />can lift it</p>
        <p begin="00:05:51.890" end="00:05:55.450" tts:direction="ltr">to create a more permanent takeaway title,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:55.450" end="00:05:58.930" tts:direction="ltr">or maybe I have a different audience that
<br />needs to make a decision.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:58.930" end="00:06:02.790" tts:direction="ltr">Now I'm going to do something like this,
<br />where it says,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:02.790" end="00:06:05.530" tts:direction="ltr">weekly training program registrations are</p>
        <p begin="00:06:05.530" end="00:06:09.770" tts:direction="ltr">50% lower compared to the highest week in
<br />May.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:09.770" end="00:06:12.130" tts:direction="ltr">Here I'm really trying to point out,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:12.130" end="00:06:13.830" tts:direction="ltr">hey, we have a problem.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:13.830" end="00:06:17.690" tts:direction="ltr">Now let's determine some actions to be
<br />able to mitigate that.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:17.690" end="00:06:20.290" tts:direction="ltr">You can certainly have that dashboard,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:20.290" end="00:06:24.755" tts:direction="ltr">and then you can lift one of those to
<br />create that explanatory chart.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:24.755" end="00:06:27.260" tts:direction="ltr">Remember, when you're crossing your T's,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:27.260" end="00:06:28.940" tts:direction="ltr">there are many different approaches.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:28.940" end="00:06:31.180" tts:direction="ltr">We have that exploratory dashboard,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:31.180" end="00:06:34.320" tts:direction="ltr">where I've got all of the various titles</p>
        <p begin="00:06:34.320" end="00:06:38.040" tts:direction="ltr">there that are helping to show what that
<br />data has,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:38.040" end="00:06:42.120" tts:direction="ltr">or I can be more explanatory where I'm
<br />providing,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:42.120" end="00:06:45.840" tts:direction="ltr">for instance, this opportunity to expand
<br />our training program.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:45.840" end="00:06:47.360" tts:direction="ltr">Here I've got that verb,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:47.360" end="00:06:50.375" tts:direction="ltr">and I've got that static detail showing
<br />that.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:50.375" end="00:06:52.730" tts:direction="ltr">Now let's talk about the tooltips.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:52.730" end="00:06:55.190" tts:direction="ltr">This is the second part of crossing your
<br />T's.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:55.190" end="00:06:57.790" tts:direction="ltr">Whenever you're using or creating
<br />tooltips,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:57.790" end="00:06:59.710" tts:direction="ltr">in tableau or another application,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:59.710" end="00:07:02.770" tts:direction="ltr">I highly recommend using sentences.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:02.770" end="00:07:07.190" tts:direction="ltr">This just helps your user connect the dots
<br />and understand the context.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:07.190" end="00:07:09.650" tts:direction="ltr">Right now, we've been using the default
<br />where we just have</p>
        <p begin="00:07:09.650" end="00:07:12.410" tts:direction="ltr">the measures or dimensions that just show
<br />up in the tooltip.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:12.410" end="00:07:15.250" tts:direction="ltr">We need to now put some intentionality
<br />towards that.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:15.250" end="00:07:17.630" tts:direction="ltr">Can also use design to emphasize.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:17.630" end="00:07:19.050" tts:direction="ltr">You might put in some color,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:19.050" end="00:07:25.830" tts:direction="ltr">you might increase a typeface size so that
<br />you can create some contrast.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:25.830" end="00:07:30.550" tts:direction="ltr">Tool tips do work better than labeling and
<br />exploratory dashboards.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:30.550" end="00:07:33.810" tts:direction="ltr">Again, you want your dashboard to be as
<br />clean as possible,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:33.810" end="00:07:36.690" tts:direction="ltr">and then as soon as your user begins to
<br />interact with it,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:36.690" end="00:07:40.070" tts:direction="ltr">they are discovering your insights, maybe
